eter X_A^i is generally unequal to factorization annihilation parameter\nX_A^f, which differ from the traditional treatment. With the fitted parameters,\nall results for observables of B_{u,d,s} ->pi pi, pi K, K K decays are in good\nagreement with experimental data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Sep 2014 08:58:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 27 Nov 2014 09:30:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-12-15"}
